Description: Rim sherd of grey ware pottery trefoil oinochoe; brown fabric core with mica inclusions; thick, very dark grey (almost black) slip on exterior; thin-walled; thickened offset rim. Slight re-curving on the neck at the left break, presumably connected with the out-turn of a trefoil mouth.
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p.260, no.2)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.166)
